87.character: 好きなのなんでも頼んじゃって

90.speaker: SASAKO

177.definition: the entertainment of sweets, since you can enjoy both the

220.character: なんなの ペッペーンって

224.speaker: S MAMA
224.character: よっぽどのことでないと 飲んじゃダメ！
224.definition: Don't drink it unless it's an emergency!

225.speaker: KING
225.character: ノドが渇けば ケーキを飲めばいいのよ！
225.definition: If you're thirsty, just gulp down some cake!

226.speaker: MAMA
226.character: でも 飲むのはいいけど
226.definition: That's fine and all, but my palate is getting bored of all the sweets.

227.speaker: S MAMA
227.character: そういうときのために…軽食というジャンルが 用意されているのよ！
227.definition: And for that very reason... They have light snacks ready for you, too.

229.character: ケーキバイキングと名乗るからにはお菓子を味わってこそ
229.definition: Since it's an all-you-can-eat cake buffet, I thought it was just for eating sweets.

230.speaker: MAMA
230.character: 軽食なんて邪道だ なんて思ってたけど
230.definition: I thought light snacks would be heresy.

232.speaker: KING
232.character: オールラウンドにケーキバイキングという空間を楽しんでこそ
232.definition: Only once you've enjoyed all that an all-you-can-eat cake buffet has to offer,

233.speaker: KING
233.character: ケーキバイキンガー！ なのよ
233.definition: can you be a true all-you-can-eat cake buffeter.

234.speaker: MAMA
234.character: お二人と 一緒に来られて よかったわ
234.definition: I'm very thankful I came with you two.

235.speaker: MAMA
235.definition: If I had come here alone, I'd—

237.speaker: MAMA
237.character: なんだか すごい達成感

238.speaker: KING
238.character: やったわね 私たち

239.speaker: S MAMA
239.definition: I didn't think you were going to be able to finish that last plate, Panda Mama.

241.speaker: MAMA
241.character: 言わないで… 恥ずかしい

242.speaker: MAMA
242.character: あら？田中さんじゃない？
242.definition: Oh, if it isn't Ms. Tanaka.

243.speaker: TANAKA
243.character: こんにちは パンダママ
243.definition: Hello, Panda Mama. Are you out running errands?

244.speaker: MAMA
244.character: それがね 田中さん 聞いてくれる？ 大充実の一日
244.definition: Well, you see, Ms. Tanaka, listen to this, I had a completely productive day. My last plate was so full!

246.speaker: MAMA
246.character: よかったら お茶でもしない？
246.definition: Would you care to join us for some tea?

247.speaker: KING
247.character: いいわね 休みたいわ ちょっと 食べ疲れしちゃったから
247.definition: That sounds great. I'd like to rest. I'm exhausted from all the eating.

248.speaker: MAMA
248.character: そういえば ここね 息子が常連なのよ
248.definition: By the way, my son's a regular here.

249.speaker: KING
249.character: あっ 息子さん バイトは続いてるの？
249.definition: Is your son still working the part-time job?

251.speaker: TANAKA
251.character: いつも 会ったら挨拶してくれるわよ
251.definition: He always says hello when I see him.

252.speaker: MAMA
252.character: 愛想だけはいいのよ でも将来が心配
252.definition: His courtesies may be his only good trait. But I'm so worried about his future.

253.speaker: KING
253.character: 家の子も カードっていうの？
253.definition: My son is playing with, what are they called, cards?

254.speaker: KING
254.character: それで遊んでばっかりいるから 心配なのよ
254.definition: He's been playing with them so much that I'm worried. Seems like everyone's in the same boat.

255.speaker: S MAMA
255.character: おかわりちょうだい 同じもの
255.definition: Oh, could I get another of the same?

256.speaker: POLAR BEAR
256.definition: Yes, ma'am. Refills are half price. Oh, my!

258.speaker: ALL
258.character: おかわりなのに お金とるの！？
258.definition: It's a refill and you're charging us money?

259.speaker: TANAKA
259.definition: It's like a café in a hotel!

260.speaker: POLAR BEAR
260.character: も… 申し訳ありません

261.speaker: S MAMA
261.definition: Isn't half price a bit expensive?

262.speaker: KING
262.character: 時々 来てるんだから サービスしなさいよ
262.definition: We come here every now and then so it should be on the house!

264.speaker: S MAMA
264.character: ホント ゆとりって怖いわ
264.definition: You can't ever let your guard down.

265.speaker: TANAKA
265.character: あら もう こんな時間？
265.definition: Oh, where did the time go?

267.speaker: POLAR BEAR
267.character: ありがとうございました

268.speaker: KING
268.character: ねぇ 今度は ランチバイキングに行きましょうよ
268.definition: Say, let's go to an all-you-can-eat lunch buffet next time.

269.speaker: S MAMA
269.definition: Sounds great! Where should we go?

270.speaker: MAMA
270.character: ちょっと 場所 教えてくれる？
270.definition: Sounds like you know a good place. I do!

271.speaker: KING
271.character: １丁目に イタリアンレストランがあるでしょ
271.definition: You know the Italian restaurant on 1st street, right?

272.speaker: KING
272.character: そこの評判がいいみたい
272.definition: I've heard great things about that place!

274.speaker: S MAMA
274.character: あら ぜひ ご一緒したいわ

275.speaker: MAMA
275.character: コーヒー おかわりいただこうかしら
275.definition: Could I get a refill on my coffee?

276.speaker: KING
276.character: おかわりの おかわりだから ４分の１のお値段でいいわよね？
276.definition: It's a refill of a refill, so it'll only be a fourth of the price, right?

277.speaker: S MAMA
277.definition: Makes perfect sense to me. I'd like a refill, too, Mr. Polar Bear.

278.speaker: KING
278.character: ああ 私も 半額の半額のおかわり もらえる？
278.definition: Oh, me, too. Could I get half price on a half price refill?

279.speaker: POLAR BEAR
279.definition: {\a6}Actually, a refill on a refill will not make it a lesser price...

282.speaker: PENGUIN
282.character: というか なんで僕まで？
282.definition: Or rather, why do I have to hide with you? {\a6}What?!

283.speaker: PANDA
283.character: ペンギンさん ペンギンさん

285.speaker: PANDA
285.character: 旅に出ると気持ちが盛り上がるね
285.definition: Isn't it exciting when we go on trips?

287.speaker: PANDA
287.character: ペンギンさん 盛り上がったまま全財産窓から投げちゃえば
287.definition: Well since you're so excited, why don't you throw your life savings out the window?

288.speaker: PENGUIN
288.character: 窓開かんないし それにそこまでは盛り上がってないかな
288.definition: The windows won't open, not to mention I'm not {\i1}that{\i0} excited.

289.speaker: PANDA
289.character: じゃペンギンさんちょっと黙っててよ 僕ねるから
289.definition: Then could you shut up for a while, Mr. Penguin? I'm gonna go to sleep.

290.speaker: PENGUIN
290.character: 君がかけてきたんだけど
290.definition: You're the one that started talking to me... Next week's Polar Bear Café,

291.speaker: POLAR BEAR
291.character: ペーパークラフトでお送りします
291.definition: will be presented to you in paper craft.
